title: 2005 Subaru Impreza WRX STi
description:
Up for sale is an Aspen White 2005 Subaru Impreza WRX STi. I am the 3rd owner of the car, the last guy just bought it from his dad. Never owned by a teenager. This car has been meticulously taken care of and it is mechanically sound and will be for a long time to come. I HAVE ALL SERVICE RECORDS AND RECEIPTS. It just passed New York State Inspection in August. This care has been tastefully modified with longevity in mind. For that reason, it has not been raced, tracked, or launched. The odometer reads 127K with about 26K on a new OEM STi block from Subaru after a blown gasket. The number will continue to go up as this is my daily driver. The turbo was replaced with a new oem one around the same time. Shifts smoothly through all six gears and pulls hard everytime. Reason for selling is that I want something a little more comfortable. Don't take that the wrong way, I love this car and it's a blast to drive, I just think it's time for a change. Here is a list of what you need to know.

Oil changed every 3-5K

Premium NGK Iridium Spark plugs installed less than 15K

Pro Drive Axel Back Exhaust 
HKS Turbo Timer 
Tune from EFI Logics

JDM Tail Light Pattern

And perhaps a few more things I forgot 
 
Bad: 
A few dents and dings from the City life. 
Tear in Steering Wheel 
 
Selling for 17,000 OBO. Open to trades. I'm looking for someone to take care of this like I have. Best way to reach me is email or text. I work full time 8-5 so be patient. Thanks

Let's use an example that you have a 1600 square feet sit down restaurant with 40 seats, serve beer and wine, serve bistro style food and have a 10' hood what should the equipment be under the hood and what size refrigeration items. Assuming a 10' hood you are required to have 6" clearance on left and right side of hood unless you have walls on both sides at end of hood so without walls you have 9' to use on equipment. We will start with a typical layout 3' for stove with 6 burners and oven with 36" salamander on top of stove, 16" for fryer 40 pound (if cooking frozen fries go to 50 pound), 36" char grill (use radiant for clean burn, char rock for flavor), 18" single or double pot stove. This is your 9' of equipment change menu or style and length of hood and equipment will change. If you need griddle we can shorten char broiler and eliminate pot stove or go to 24" range or cook top. On refrigeration you would need at least 48" in sandwich/ salad prep refrigeration normal would be 72" if you have room in walkways go with Mega for more food pans (mega is 7" deeper front to back). Should have a 2 door freezer (I prefer bottom mount compressor) but depending on items may get by with 1 door freezer. On refrigeration a small walk in 6' by 6' is best but at least a 3 door refrigerator bottom mount compressor. On bar you have several choices I would need to talk with you to make recommendations. There are many things to discuss from type of chair and layout and so on. I can provide more than just to sell you an item.
  
 
Let's TALK REBATES
  
   
Across the USA many utility companies offer excellent rebates on many of the products we sell for being energy star. Rebates run from $50 to $600 on refrigeration/ freezer items. For example Edison offers on stainless solid door freezers $300 for a 2 door and $600 for a 3 door, on glass door freezers they offer $500 for 2 door. Rebates are easy to apply for and it is nice to get funds from utility company. Call us on more details.
   
  
SHOULD I BUY NEW OR USED?
   
  
It is always nice to save money what about good used equipment? Many refrigerators will last up to 20 years but I consider the life span to be 10 years so if a unit is 10 to 15 years old there is no real value for the unit even if it is working today and if it is 8 years old you may get some use out of it. It is common that a customer will tell me they found a 2-year-old 2 door freezer for $2000. When I look up the serial numbers it may be 15 plus years' old I find it not to be working properly and really no value. On working correctly, they say it cools down, but working and working correctly can be a BIG difference. For a freezer it must reach 0 degrees to negative 10 degrees, on refrigerator it must be between 33 degrees and 40 degrees. So a freezer at 10 degrees and refrigerator at 45 degrees are working but will not pass health inspection. When you buy used they usually don't have a warranty, you have to arrange transport. If it is only a couple years old and it is super cheap you can consider it, but please do not pay a lot for an old unit that may be full of headaches. Many times I am able to sell a NEW unit at a similar price to what others will sell used AND it has full warranty. 
   
  
   
  
 
GENE SHOOK RESTAURANT EQUIPMENT  
12583 Crenshaw Blvd  
Hawthorne, CA 90250  
 
Phone: 310 292-1182

title: R2000 Saeco-Cannondale "Cipollini Equipped" 57cm Dura-Ace Spinergy
description:
I've built this 2000 Cannondale R2000 Saeco-Cannondale team bicycle to replicate the racing machine of the legendary sprinter Mario Cipollini. The bike is equipped with a Shimano Dura-Ace 7700 component group, and is highlighted by the funky Cinelli Alter stem (hard-to-find in team colors) and Spinergy Wheels. The carbon fork is made by TIME, but is branded CODA Slice Echelon.  
 
Here are the bicycle's wonderful specs: Shimano Dura-Ace 9-speed gruppo, including CRANKSET (172.5mm, 53x39t chainrings), SHIFTER/BRAKE LEVERS, DERAILLEURS (both), BRAKES and CHAIN.  Other parts: HEADSET- Aheadset, HANDLEBAR- Cinelli Nerve 44cm with NEW Fizik bar tape, STEM- Cinelli Alter 115mm, SEATPOST- Cannondale, SADDLE- Selle Italia Prolink (if you want one of those rare/expensive "Lion King" personalized saddles, go for it!), TIRES- Vittoria Rubino Pro Slick III and BOTTLE CAGES - Elite Ciussi 
 
I actually live near Philadelphia, but would be willing to meet you in north Jersey area, since I have family nearby. I rebuild/restore/refurbish bicycles (vintage and modern) in my basement shop. You can check out some of my work via my Cycle Tech Royersford page on Facebook or my blog at http://cycletechrofo.blogspot.com

title: 2013 Honda CBR250R (With ABS)
description: Sup CL, I'm selling my 2013 Honda CBR250r (ABS) motorcycle, with the rare black/black color combo which was only available from Honda on the 2013-2014 models. The motorcycle is in amazing condition, and has been stored in a secure professional parking garage, and has been covered with a Nelson-rigg bike cover whenever it was not being ridden. Only reason I'm selling the bike is because this was my first bike, had it since July 2016 and was ready for something a little more powerful, so I just upgraded to a 2015 Suzuki GSX-R 600, and don't see the sense of having two motorcycles. This is literally the best first motorcycle a person can buy, it is also amazing for commuting, I literally average around 66-71mpg with this bike, and even though my GSX-R 600 is faster, i still ride this bike more, because its comfortable, light as a feather, and fun as hell when you get it in the 6000-8000 rpm range. The bike has never been dropped, tipped over, nor abused. The oil was just changed, aswell as the chain was just inspected, cleaned, and lubed by KING CYCLES late November 2016. The bike does have a Pro-Grip Tank Pad to protect the bike from scratches when your riding in a leaned over position, aswell as a aftermarket 2Bros Carbon Fiber Black Series exhaust slip-on, which was professionally installed by KING CYCLES, and a Perilli Sport Demon rear tire (one of the best motorcycle tires) with plenty of life in them . The bike will also come with the original exhaust, even though I don't recommend putting it back on because it's very quiet, and New York has some of the worst drivers I've ever came across. For new riders, please get a motorcycle with ABS, it will protect you from idiots on the road, and potentially save your life, please don't listen to people saying you don't need ABS, take it from someone who's been riding motorcycles for 7 months now, ABS has saved my ass more than I can count from bad drivers, and bad roads. It's well worth the extra money. The motorcycle has a clean title, and only has 1,140 miles but will go up, since I still ride it whenever we get nice weather. The bike comes with 2 keys, a Nelson-rigg bike cover, a yellow brake disc lock (w/Key), and the original Honda exhaust slip-on. The bike does not need anything but a new owner, you won't even need to buy gas, because it will have a full tank of gas when it's sold. The price is non-negotiable, I'm not desperate for money, or to sell the bike. Thanks for checking my baby out,  Happy New Years to all! Please Note: For your safety, aswell as my bike's safety I will be the one test riding the bike while you follow behind me.

title: treadmill and bike
description:
NordicTrack Treadmill T8.0  
 
The T8.0 is the perfect mix of technology and performance. Featuring iFit Live, you can quickly connect to the internet and download your latest workout straight to your machine. With a maximum speed of 18 km/h and incline of 10%, the T8.0 will challenge even the most experienced runner.  The T8.0 treadmill features advanced technology and durable build quality that makes NordicTrack world leaders in home fitness equipment. iFit compatible, you can connect to the web in no time and download new workouts and maps to keep you motivated. You will also be provided with tips and advice during iFit trainer workouts from experts including celebrities like Jillian Michaels, or you can choose to attach your mp3 player and workout to your favourite music on the Intermix Acoustics sound system. With 1-Touch 10% incline and speeds of up to 18 km/h, you can enjoy the machine with manual control or with one of the 16 pre-programmed workouts. FlexPath cushioning protects your joints from impact and the textured walk belt provides the traction you need to feel safe and secure whilst running. this treadmill delivers smarter workouts and faster results! Featuring workouts Powered by Google Maps™, training with Jillian Michaels and automatic speed and incline controls, this wireless technology is the ultimate workout experience! And, with a DurX™ Commercial Pro Motor, you'll run safer, longer and quieter. It's our smoothest, quietest motor available today! Other features include an extra-long 20 x 60 treadbelt with DuraStride™ Response Cushioning, a Compatible Music Port for iPod®** and an included Polar® wireless chest pulse strap.

NordicTrack Upright Exercise Cycle GX2.0 
 
 
Pedal Your Way to Health with the NordicTrack Upright Bike Pile on the miles with a smooth and comfortable ride atop the NordicTrack Upright Bike and watch those pounds melt away. Easy to put together, use and move around, this good-looking stationary bike gets you going with great exercise without any fuss right away. The NordicTrack GX2.0 bike is designed to keep you working out longer and harder thanks to its advanced comfort and safety features. An oversized adjustable seat guarantees you a cushy workout, and the vertical and horizontal adjustments help you find the perfect fit and posture. No more worrying about losing balance or your feet flying off when you go too fast since the pedals come with adjustable straps that keep your feet secure and your mind focused on your workout. The dual- position adjustable handlebars help you find the best posture while working out and maximize your efforts thanks to the built in sensors that monitor your heart rate and ensure you're in the right training zone at all times. Exercising no longer has to be a deafening experience either. The upright bike operates so quietly that you can converse with others, enjoy your TV shows or just enjoy the silence while riding. The smooth, frictionless resistance system also allows you to adjust your workout intensity with the simple touch of a button. The GX2 Upright also incorporates the innovative wireless  iFit Live™* technology featuring exercises powered by Google Maps™ for a simulated course over hills and plains, training with Jillian Michaels and much more, giving you the ultimate high-tech workout experience. You can customize your own program for achieving specific goals or choose from 18 motivating built-in workouts that automatically adjust the resistance of the bike to increase intensity and burn more calories. Other features like the cool Grafixx™ Display feature, music port for iPOD®, and a built-in sound system help keep you having fun and motivated. The NordicTrack Upright Bike gives you the solid reliability that you expect in an exercise machine with the high-tech features that elevate your workout experience from typical to exceptional.

Video Features 
 
Super Contrast Panel: The Samsung F8500 series Plasma TV's new Super Contrast Panel delivers incredible brightness, contrast, and clarity. Larger Red/Green/Blue sub-pixel color areas within the panel create a picture that rivals LED-LCD TVs for brightness. To further improve the already impressive picture, the Super Contrast Panel combines two key innovations for enhanced black levels and color reproduction 
 
Real Black Pro II: Through technology advancement to both the hardware and software of the TV, you can now experience a richer picture quality with deeper blacks, bolder color, and higher contrast. By improving the reflection reduction proprieties of the panel, combined with improving the reset pulse algorithm in the software, you can get the most cinematic viewing experience in a bright or dark room. 
Wide Color Enhancer Plus: Wide Color Enhancer Plus allows you to see picture color the way the director originally intended. Witness the entire RGB spectrum brought to life on your screen to bring you exceptionally vibrant, yet natural-looking images faithful to the director's original intent. 
Clear Image Technology: The Samsung F8500 series Plasma TV employs two advanced Clear Image technologies which help eliminate blurring caused by off-axis viewing or fast motion video. 
 
Single Layer Panel: The Plasma TV employs a single layer panel structure which eliminates the production of dual images and blurring, especially at off angled viewing. 
600Hz Subfield Motion: The Samsung F8500 series Plasma TV generates a frame of video at 600 times per second. The result is smoother images with unprecedented picture quality, especially beneficial when viewing sports and fast action movies. 
Cinema Smooth Plus: Movies are shot at 24 fps (frames per second); Cinema Smooth Plus is a refined playback process of 24p movies from Blu-ray and Satellite TV sources that accurately converts and displays content originally shot on film at 24fps as compared to the 30fps of DVD and Blu-ray disc. This allows for smoother motion scenes when watching sources shot at the standard movie rate of 24fps. 
 
HDTV Tuner: The TV has built-in over-the-air HDTV (ATSC) and Digital Cable (QAM) tuners, so you don't need a separate set-top box to receive and decode over-the-air HDTV/SDTV or unencrypted Digital Cable signals. 
 
1080p Resolution: The Samsung F8500 series Plasma TV displays all inputs at a resolution of 1080p (1920 x 1080). The television's HDMI and component video inputs will accept 1080p (24/60Hz), 1080i, 720p, 480p and 480i video signals. 
 
HDMI (v.1.4): The Samsung Plasma TV features four HDMI 1.4 inputs to connect to your Blu-ray/DVD player, Satellite/Cable receiver, or AV receiver. All HDMI inputs support x.v.Color, Deep Color, 3D, and CEC. The HDMI 3 input also supports the ARC function. The HDMI 4 input is MHL (Mobile High-Definition Link) compliant. In addition, any HDMI input can be used to connect a PC to this TV. 
Component Video: The Plasma TV features a single component video input. The TV's component video input can also be used as a composite video input (480i only). 
HDMI (MHL) Port: The HDMI 4 port is designed for the connection of select mobile phones and other portable electronic devices using the new MHL (Mobile High-Definition Link) standard. Simply plug your MHL compatible smartphone into the TV's HDMI 4 (MHL) port using the HDMI cable that is included with your mobile phone. MHL allows you to display full 1080p video and still images on the Samsung TV from your mobile smartphone. The TV's IR remote can be used to control basic playback functions (such as Play/Pause, Stop Fast Forward/Rewind, and Menu navigation). Your MHL compliant device will also charge while connected to the TV's HDMI 4 port. To find MHL-certified devices, go to www.mhlconsortium.org. 
 
Full HD 3D (via HDMI 1.4): The Samsung F8500 series Plasma TV offers Full HD (1080p) 3D capability. Samsung 3D TV utilizes Bluetooth-enabled active shutter glasses (two pair included) for a full 1080p 3D viewing experience when coupled with a 3D source, such as a 3D-ready Blu-ray player or an HD 3D broadcast from satellite or cable providers (connected via HDMI 1.4). The Samsung F8500 series Plasma TV automatically adjusts the overall picture to provide an optimal 3D effect. The Samsung 3D TV also offers a unique feature that allows you to intensify your 2D viewing experience by up-converting it to virtual 3D. In addition, you can adjust the overall 3D perspective (+/-5) and overall 3D image depth (1-10). Samsung 3D TV supports Full HD 3D for 1920 x 2205p (24Hz) or 1280 x 1470p (60Hz) video signals; and virtual 3D for 1920 x 1080p (24/30/60Hz), 1920 x 1080i (60Hz), or 1280 x 720p (60hz) video signals. The Samsung F8500 series Plasma TV offers various 3D modes to match your 3D viewing needs. 
 
2D-3D: Changes a 2D image to 3D; you can adjust the focus and depth of the image to maximize 3D experience. 
Side-by-Side: Displays two images next to each other. Available when the resolution is 720p, 1080i or 1080p. 
Top & Bottom: Displays one image above another. Available when the resolution is 720p, 1080i or 1080p. 
3D-2D: Displays the image for the left eye only. 
Off: Turns the 3D function off. 
Note: 2010 Samsung IR 3D glasses and3D glasses from other manufacturers are not compatible. Some 3D modes may not be available depending on the format of the image source. PIP, Auto Program, and some Picture Adjustment functions will also be disabled in 3D mode. 
Included 3D Glasses (4 pair): The Samsung F8500 series Plasma TV includes four pair of 3D active glasses with built-in Bluetooth. Samsung's 3D Active Glasses (SSG-5100GB) offer a comfortable fit through its lightweight frame and flexible noise- and ear-pieces. The Samsung 3D Active Glasses are powered by a single CR2025 3V lithium coin-type battery (pre-installed). The battery can last up to 150 hours when powered on. The Samsung's 3D Active Glasses provide a viewing range between 6.5' and 19.5' from the Samsung 3D-ready TV.

title: Line6 Pod HD500X
description:
This HD500X has been lightly used and never gigged. It's a great FX processor but I have too much gear and we just moved to a new Manhattan apartment so a bunch of stuff has to go.  
 
Here is a link to a video about the HD500X: 
 
  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aZJMSEZcS5o 
 
And here is the generic description of the HD500X from Guitar Center:  
 
The POD HD500X is the ultimate tone palette, whether you want to re-create classics or go somewhere new with the ability to recall up to 512 totally different rigs-with changes to preamp type, power amp configuration, guitar type, polyphonic alt-tuning, effects chain and more. And thanks to HD technology, POD HD500X provides the depth, character and touch nuance to inspire your creativity in the studio or on stage. So if you've never experienced the flagship of the POD family, now's the time to check out POD HD500X. 
 
World-Class HD Amps 
From vintage classics to modern powerhouses, each HD amp delivers incredible sonic depth, character and touch nuance to inspire your playing-and that's just the beginning. Customize the tone and dynamic response of each HD amp with an extensive set of deep parameters including Sag, Bias, Bias Excursion, Hum and more. 
 
100+ Studio and Stomp Effects 
POD HD500X gives you over 100 studio and boutique stomp effects, so you can take your sound in any direction. Emulate classic signal chains with distortions, delays, mods, filters, reverbs and more, or discover entirely new sounds by mixing and matching up to eight simultaneous effects. You also get pro-grade, assignable footswitches and a built-in, die-cast expression pedal to control your effects in real time. 
 
More Processing Power, More Creativity 
With unparalleled flexibility and more processing power than anything in its class, POD HD500X is built for tone creation. To start, POD features dynamic DSP, so you have the freedom to stack the effects you want wherever you want them. Compared to its predecessor, POD HD500X lets you add even more effects to your signal chain. You can also mix and match HD amps, cabinets, mics and effects in virtually endless combinations. With 512 presets, you've got plenty of options for recalling your tones. 
 
Sculpt Sounds with Dual Signal Paths 
Legendary guitar tones are often created with more than one signal path. POD HD500X lets you create these complex, rich tones without the setup headaches of traditional dual-amp rigs. You can route your guitar through two completely independent paths-each with its own HD amp and effects chain, of course-or process two signals at once using the 1/4" guitar, 1/4" auxiliary or XLR mic inputs. So whether you want to configure elaborate signal chains for more traditional stereo amp setups, or create unique soundscapes, you've picked the right tool. 
 
Assignable Footswitches and Rugged Construction 
With POD HD500X, you get professional-grade footswitches with bright LED rings for at-a-glance operation. You can use them to enable or bypass amps and effects, or to select presets directly. If you want to get more creative, you can assign multiple amp and effects parameters to the expression pedal and morph between sounds-controlling up to 52 parameters in real time. The footswitches also control the built-in 48-second looper-an instrument unto itself. The bent-metal chassis and rugged construction make POD HD500X ideal for any stage. 
 
Flexible I/O for Recording with Any DAW 
POD HD500X provides all the connections you need for studio, stage and anywhere in between. You can plug in a mic to record vocals or acoustic instruments, track with your favorite HD amps, use the stereo FX loop to connect stompboxes and outboard effects, and much more. Connect to your computer via USB for multi-channel, studio-quality recording with your favorite DAW software-or tap into POD HD Edit, the free editor/librarian software that makes it easy to tweak and organize all your tones. 
 
Command Center for Your Guitar Experience 
It doesn't matter if you use a guitar amp, go straight to the PA or take advantage of a next-gen full-range guitar rig-POD HD500X is the ideal command center for any guitar setup. It's a fully assignable MIDI controller, so you can use the footswitches and expression pedal to control all kinds of external hardware and software-and it gets even better when you use POD HD500X with other Line 6 gear. 
 
Features: 
 
Extensive collection of award-winning HD amps for authentic tone and feel 
100+ studio and stomp effects"use up to eight simultaneously 
Selectable speaker cabinets and mics 
Unparalleled flexibility to craft your tones: Dual signal paths, multiple routing optionso Dynamic DSP with more power for amps and effects and stereo FX loop can be inserted anywhere in the signal chain 
Professional-grade footswitches with bright LED rings for at-a-glance operation 
Comprehensive I/O includes USB 2.0, MIDI, S/PDIF, balanced XLR outputs, integrated mic preamp and more 
Guitar input with variable impedance 
Fully assignable MIDI controller"control external hardware and software via footswitches and expression pedal 
L6 LINK connection for integration and control of DT-series amplifiers and StageSource series loudspeakers 
VDI connection for integration and control of James Tyler Variax guitars 
8 set lists containing 64 presets 
512 user-writable preset locations 
Assignable expression pedal controls amp and effect parameters 
Integrated 48-second looper with dedicated footswitch 
Built-in chromatic tuner 
Tap-tempo footswitch 
Professional-grade construction with bent metal chassis, chrome roll bar and die-cast expression pedal

title: Burton Harvest 147 Snowboard
description:
Good condition, minor scratches on base but no gouges or PTEX repairs.  Recently tuned, great edges. 
 
Core Material: Super Fly II with DualZone EGD 
Base Material: Sintered 
Construction Materials: Triax Fiberglass with Carbon I-Beam 
Shape: Twin 
Sidewalls: 10:45 
Camber: Camber Bend 
Binding Type: The Channel - EST, Re:Flex, Disc 
Feel: 5 
Extras: Squeezebox, Jumper Cables Hi-Voltage, Frostbite Edges, Ellip Kicks, Pro-Tip and Infinite Ride 
Nug Raduction Level: 10 (Downsize 8 to 10cm from normal board length) 
Part of the Burton Restricted lineup of specialty sticks, this camber style board is for intermediate park riders who like to reap what they sow.  
 
The Harvest builds on the Nug, a shorter amped up board designed to make easy work of spins and jumps. This board has an even smaller mid section, but with added camber and softer flex for better overall handling. Technical features include Squeezebox, a system of thick and thin core sections that transfers energy outward from the feet; 10:45 Sidewalls for maximum impact absorption; and Hi-Voltage Jumper Cables, ultra light carbon strings that radiate from the feet towards the tip and tale, creating more snap and pop. Also, Pro-Tip tapered tip and tail enhances mobility of this board, while Frostbite Edges help you really dig in in the ice. The Harvest snowboard also comes with a standard sintered base, which takes wax easily and effectively, and Infinite Ride technology, a process by which the board is built up and then broken in for longevity in performance and durability.  
 
If you are looking for a shorter board with extraordinary control and mobility, go with this high-end board. The Harvest will be abundant.

title: RC
description:
Dominus TR truck, it's for a hobbyist RC enthusiast! *Not a toy version, for adults as a hobby sport*  
$150 is price, it is in like new condition.  
 
Details about the truck: 
You can put a go Pro camera on it, it drives fast, can make it over ramps, bumps, dirt tracks, in the snow, etc. controller (transmitter) is not specific to a certain vehicle.....I use the same controller for all of my vehicles.  If you are planning to purchase more than 1 vehicle, I would look into purchasing a transmitter that can do the same.  Same goes for my batteries. All of my batteries are interchangeable with all of my vehicles.   
Spektrum makes a good transmitter.  I use spektrum for my cars/trucks as well as for my airplanes/helicopters.  Very reliable.  They make a whole line of transmitters, from beginer to advanced.  You can probably pick up a used entry level/intermediate transmitter for under $50, which will control any vehicles you purchase in the future, so you dont have to continue to purchase a controller for each vehicle. 
For batterries, I use Zippy batteries fro hobbyking.  Zippy is an economical but reliable battery.  I would not get into other chinese batteries other than Zippy.  For cars and trucks you want to make sure that you purchase hard case batteries.  This truck can run Lipo batteries, 2s or 3s.

title: Boss ME-80 Guitar Multi-Effects Pedal
description:
For Sale:  BOSS ME-80 
 
Barely used . . .   Never taken out of the apartment.  Great effects!  Battery operated or with power supply. 
 
http://www.musiciansfriend.com/amplifiers-effects/boss-me-80-guitar-multi-effects-pedal 
 
Packed with tons of awesome BOSS effects and ready to hit the stage, the ME-80 is the perfect compact tone processor for gigging guitarists. A user-friendly, knob-based interface makes it quick and easy to dial in great sounds, with the flexibility of individual stompbox-style on/off or instant recall of complex multi-effects setups. Unique footswitches deliver even more control than previous designs for efficient and intuitive effects switching, patch selection, and realtime sound shaping while playing. It also includes free BOSS TONE STUDIO software to help you unlock even more tonal possibilities, plus a web connection to BOSS TONE CENTRAL for direct access to free patches created by pro guitarists and much more. 
 
Find your own personal sound with the ME-80s extensive range of built-in effects. A complete history of gig-ready BOSS tone processing is at your command, from multiple overdrives and distortions to wahs, mod effects, pitch shifters, delays, and beyond. BOSS groundbreaking Multi-Dimensional Processing (MDP) technology is represented with the unique, spacious ambience of Tera Echo and the distinctive tone-shaping possibilities of Overtone. Updated COSM preamps include new additions such as Crunch and Metal, plus an AC preamp designed for acoustic/electric guitar. 
 
Unlike typical menu-driven multi-effects processors that are complicated and unintuitive, using the ME-80 is as easy as using a stompbox. Effects are organized into eight logical categories that can all be active at the same time. Seven categories contain multiple effects types to choose from, plus dedicated knobs for selecting a type and adjusting it with a set of parameters youd find in the pedal version of the effect. The Pedal FX category has its own knob for quickly assigning a particular effects type or function to be controlled by foot with the expression pedal. You can even save all the current knob settings to one of the ME-80s 36 user patch locations. 
The hands-on experience that stomp box control provides is perfect for tweaking tones as you go. In Manual mode, the categories function like individual stomp effects, with instant adjustment via the panel knobs and on/off control with dedicated footswitches. By entering Memory mode, seven footswitches are automatically reconfigured to select user or preset patches and patch banks, letting you recall complete multi-effects setups directly. One footswitch on the ME-80 is dedicated just for mode switching, so you can toggle between Manual and Memory modes any time you want. 
FEATURES 
Compact and powerful floor multi-effects with a simple knob-based interface 
Eight simultaneous effects categories, each with multiple effects types 
Dial up tones with the ease of using your favorite stompboxes 
Includes a massive selection of top-quality effects, from classic BOSS stomps to the latest MDP effects 
Updated flagship-level COSM amps derived from the GT-100 
Eight multifunction footswitches and expression pedal 
Manual mode for stomp box-style on/off; Memory mode for switching complete patch setups 
Delay section includes Phrase Loop function with 38 seconds of recording 
Runs on six AA batteries or optional PSA-series AC adapter 
USB audio/MIDI interface built in 
Free BOSS TONE STUDIO software allows you to edit and organize tones on your computer, and also preview and download free patches directly from the BOSS TONE CENTRAL website

title: 1968 Ford Thunderbird Rare Tripple Black 429 Thunderjet Coupe
description:
I am selling my 1968 Ford T-Bird Tripple Black Coupe. This is a matching number vehicle from top to bottom inside and out. Has been family owned since it was brand new. It has really been a blast to own and has always been a turn key type of car with no issues at all. Can easily and effortlessly be driven cross country. This Thunderbird turns heads everywhere it goes and gets compliments all the time. Thunderbird collectors or enthusiasts Do Not let this bird fly away without at least taking a look at this one. This car is in Showroom condition. Winner of numerous trophies from various car shows. No Bubbles No Chips No Rust No Scratches No Dings No Waves and most definitely No Bondo. The Engine is a 429 4V Thunderjet Motor with A.C. and power steering with power brakes. The Interior is jet black with bucket seats in excellent condition with no rips or torn material. The stainless steel trim in the interior has never been dinged or faded or scratched. Has the original telescopic tilt away steering wheel. Has Cobra Snakeskin exterior roof. Front and rear interior and exterior power vents still work as they should. This T-Bird has been well taken care of since it was brand new from day 1. Never smoked in and owned by non smokers. Never driven in the rain never mind the snow. Always kept inside a climate controlled garage and used during summer months only. Original owner was extremely anal on keeping up with maintenance service and has always been serviced at the local Ford dealership and always hand washed the car. Never been to a car wash. I am not car dealer I am a collector/enthusiast/hobbyist who enjoys these type of cars. Today you could not fully restore a car like this for my asking price. Never mind trying to find a good clean one to begin with. These type of cars in this type of condition are getting extremely harder and harder to find. If you do not believe me do some research and you will see there is less than a handful of 1968 Tripple Black 429 Thunderjet coupes for sale. They are extremely rare to find in this color combo. Vehicle is located in Boston Mass off I-95 and I will assist in shipping worldwide. If interested please feel free to email me through the eBay email service or call me direct at Six One Seven Four Eight Three Zero Five Zero Two and I will be happy to answer any questions you might have. No Disappointments here. Had a few say "Yea but it is not a suicide 4 door" Well if you want 4 suicide doors then go check out a 60s Lincoln not a Thunderjet coupe. These pictures do not do the car any justice at all. Actually they totally suck. Must be seen in person and driven to really appreciate it. Thanks for looking and best of luck on your classic car search. Price is Negotiable and Trades will be considered for a pre 1972

Details about the truck: 
You can put a go Pro camera on it, it drives fast, can make it over ramps, bumps, dirt tracks, in the snow, etc. controller (transmitter) is not specific to a certain vehicle.....I use the same controller for all of my vehicles.  If you are planning to purchase more than 1 vehicle, I would look into purchasing a transmitter that can do the same.  Same goes for my batteries. All of my batteries are interchangeable with all of my vehicles.   
Spektrum makes a good transmitter.  I use spektrum for my cars/trucks as well as for my airplanes/helicopters.  Very reliable.  They make a whole line of transmitters, from beginer to advanced.  You can probably pick up a used entry level/intermediate transmitter for under $50, which will control any vehicles you purchase in the future, so you dont have to continue to purchase a controller for each vehicle. 
For batterries, I use Zippy batteries fro hobbyking.  Zippy is an economical but reliable battery.  I would not get into other chinese batteries other than Zippy.  For cars and trucks you want to make sure that you purchase hard case batteries.  This truck can run Lipo batteries, 2s or 3s.

title: 2013 Honda CBR250R (With ABS)
description: Sup CL, I'm selling my 2013 Honda CBR250r (ABS) motorcycle, with the rare black/black color combo which was only available from Honda on the 2013-2014 models. The motorcycle is in amazing condition, and has been stored in a secure professional parking garage, and has been covered with a Nelson-rigg bike cover whenever it was not being ridden. Only reason I'm selling the bike is because this was my first bike, had it since July 2016 and was ready for something a little more powerful, so I just upgraded to a 2015 Suzuki GSX-R 600, and don't see the sense of having two motorcycles. This is literally the best first motorcycle a person can buy, it is also amazing for commuting, I literally average around 66-71mpg with this bike, and even though my GSX-R 600 is faster, i still ride this bike more, because its comfortable, light as a feather, and fun as hell when you get it in the 6000-8000 rpm range. The bike has never been dropped, tipped over, nor abused. The oil was just changed, aswell as the chain was just inspected, cleaned, and lubed by KING CYCLES late November 2016. The bike does have a Pro-Grip Tank Pad to protect the bike from scratches when your riding in a leaned over position, aswell as a aftermarket 2Bros Carbon Fiber Black Series exhaust slip-on, which was professionally installed by KING CYCLES, and a Perilli Sport Demon rear tire (one of the best motorcycle tires) with plenty of life in them . The bike will also come with the original exhaust, even though I don't recommend putting it back on because it's very quiet, and New York has some of the worst drivers I've ever came across. For new riders, please get a motorcycle with ABS, it will protect you from idiots on the road, and potentially save your life, please don't listen to people saying you don't need ABS, take it from someone who's been riding motorcycles for 7 months now, ABS has saved my ass more than I can count from bad drivers, and bad roads. It's well worth the extra money. The motorcycle has a clean title, and only has 1,140 miles but will go up, since I still ride it whenever we get nice weather. The bike comes with 2 keys, a Nelson-rigg bike cover, a yellow brake disc lock (w/Key), and the original Honda exhaust slip-on. The bike does not need anything but a new owner, you won't even need to buy gas, because it will have a full tank of gas when it's sold. The price is non-negotiable, I'm not desperate for money, or to sell the bike. Thanks for checking my baby out,  Happy New Years to all! Please Note: For your safety, aswell as my bike's safety I will be the one test riding the bike while you follow behind me,

title: Getting Married? Order your dress HERE
description:
HI! 
Getting married will be the BEST DAY OF YOUR LIFE!  
 
When buying the wedding dress, women don't make a purchase; they make AN INVESTMENT.  
Its an emotional investment.  
 
So it's said that you should NOT go shopping for a dress. A pre made dress; you MUST make it specially for YOU. Even though, you have already a dress, you must consider doing special adaptation and modifications to suit you the BEST.  
 
I have been in the Bridal business for MANY years and I truly understand a woman's needs for this; a special and unique day in our lives. I became a Wedding gown designer and restoration artist out of pure passion since early in life... I have been there in all type of trends and bridal's movements, wedding shows and all you can imagine. I have a very development Wedding IQ! 
 
Get in touch and let's talk about your wedding and your dress. Whether is a year ahead or in 3 weeks we can work together to make it happen accordingly! 
My rates are the most affordable in the custom made business and adapted specially for the client. 
 
I am also a Bridesmaid assistant PRO. I can also be there for you on your wedding day, making sure it all goes 100% the way it should, in the fitting and getting ready moments. 
I can assist your bridesmaids, mom, mother in law, sister with their dresses too and work out a nice package for all of you. 
I can also assist with PERFECT AFFORDABLE jewelry for the occasion!  
But as I said: lets talk!  
 
Email me with your name and number and preferred time to call you. I'd LOVE to hear your story! 
 
HAVE A BLESSED DAY! 
 
 
ADRIENN 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
#wedding #bride #bridesmaid #assistant #dress #gown #weddingparty #gettingmarried #affordable #jewlery

title: New Torker Interurban Men's and Women's Mixte Road Bikes and More!
description:
Happy 2017 Cycling Season! 
 
Please click on the Google Map to find us on the location map click on the at this location Bronx River Bicycle Works to pull up our business listing then you can link to the Reviews and or our website which we are updating away and is pretty nice most people tell me our Reviews are Spectacular and we have lots of New Bicycles to Sell! 
 
We had our Best Season Ever 2016 so it's a great time to visit our website or reviews off the Google map to get to our business page, website and Spectacular Reviews as per above. 
 
This Bike has Been Upgraded with Fantastic Continental Tires Ultra Sport Plus 116 psi Tires to make the bicycle much faster than the original stock Kenda Tires with Stop Flat II Tire Puncture Protection Liners, Velox French Cotton Rim Tapes Improved Pedals and the Nylon Strapless Mini-Clips which all my customers love as they let you Bond with the Bicycle without being Bound to it! 
 
See my website for more detailed specifics of these Upgrades! 
 
A good hard look at the New Torker Interurban gives reason to smile as it is an economically designed bike with definite component advantages over comparably priced bicycles in the IBD Independent Bicycle Dealer world. 
 
The Interurban is a fast rolling road bike with a smooth riding double butted chromoly frame with all the fittings and clearances to accommodate wider tires and lots of accessories. The Shimano STI integrated brake/shift levers, and the lightweight FSA alloy crankset make for fast and smooth shifting while quick stopping dual pivot brakes, 16 speeds and lightweight alloy wheels make this a nimble road, commuter or touring bike. Also available in a 44cm mixte style frame which an awesome remake of the Classic Mixte Road Bikes of the past with a frame which suits shorter 5'2" people in the shorter 44cm sizing range but which can be fitted for even those approaching 5'10" and taller hard to beat for it's sizing versatility. 
 
Specifications 
Frame Chromoly double butted with 130mm rear spacing 
Fork Hi-Ten 1/18" rigid 
Sizes 44, 48, 50, 52, 54, 56cm 
Headset Steel Threadless 1-1/8A 
Spacers Alloy (2-10mm, 2-5mm) 
Stem Forged alaminum 
Handlebar Aluminum drop bar W420mm 
Grip Cork 
Saddle XLC w/steel rails 
Seat Post Alloy 27.2mm x 350mm 
Seat Post Clamp Alloy 31.8mm 
Rims Alex DA 16 double wall 
Front Hub Alloy 32H QR 
Rear Hub Alloy 32H QR 
Spokes 14 guage stainless steel 
Tires Kenda 700 x28C                        Now Upgraded with Fantastic Continental Tires!!!  
Crankset FSA Tempo Compact 34-50T 
Bottom Bracket Square Taper 68mm 
Shifters/Brake Levers Shimano 2300 STI 
Derailleur-Rear Shimano Tiagra 
Derailleur-Front Shimano 2300 
Cassette Shimano HG 50 13-26T 
Chain KMC Z72 
Brakes Pro Max alloy dual pivot caliper 
Pedals Aluminum with toe clips 
 
All this is Lovingly Assembled with Strapless Nylon Toeclips which don't tie your feet to the pedals but enable you to ride vigorously comfortably and let you relax and enjoy riding while still pedaling effectively. The Strapless Toeclips let you ride all out or gently come to balanced stops able to remove a foot and stop without pause, drag, delay as second nature after the first few rides also you can get off the saddle and float like race horse jockey relaxed using the knees as shock absorbers and dismounts are seamless as all levels of riding confidence are so simply enhanced. An avid lifelong cyclist who had sworn off toeclips generally as many do tried them along with her tuneup and reported "she never had ridden so effectively nor so enjoyably"! Additionally my other Wondrous Upgrade is the Stop Flat II Tire Puncture Protection Liners which enabled me to go from 40 or so flats per year to 4 overnight! Basic Bicycle Equipment as it stops both glass in urban environments and thorns in back road desert environments from creating tube punctures and goes from old tires into new ones potentially sparing 100's of flats over the lifetime of usage depending on your amount of riding and a Forged Alloy USA Made Greenfield kickstand all as Upgrades with Taxes as Included as Lovingly Assembled $750 Done! 
 
Many more wonderful bicycles, unicycles, scooters, and Pedal Assisted Electrical Hybrids are available by reviewing our shop Weblink and going to the Product Lines Pages to review the incredible bicycle manufacturing heritage of each of our suppliers... 
 
We Also Provide Complete Bicycle Repair described as "Awesome is an Understatement" and Upgrade Servicing as well as sell Used Bicycles. 
 
We Accept Unwanted Bicycles to Recycle into Sustainable Transportation.

Some available Closeout Deals are too good to believe on fantastic bicycles let us check available opportunities or just enjoy our 2016 or newly arriving 2017 models as Upgraded, Discounted and Lovingly Assembled.

title: Profoto Pro-7B 1200 w/s Power Pack 1 Light KIT
description:
We are cleaning up the studio and have some great Profoto equipment for sale. Start your year off with a new location lighting kit by Profoto. 
 
The Profoto 1200 Watt/Second Battery Powered Pack is the go-to for location photographers worldwide. This is the perfect starter kit with a 1200w/s pack, one Pro-7 head (not the standard 7b travel head but a full Pro 7 Head) and some very expensive extras that make it a great value. Everything you need for great location lighting in one tiny package. 
 
Built to last, this battery powered kit is small enough for location and strong enough for the studio. The kit includes: 
 
(1) Profoto Pro-7b 1200 Watt/Second Battery Powered Pack 
(2) Profoto Pro-B Battery Cassettes (both batteries were recelled in 2014 - work like new) 
(1) Pro-7 Flash Head (not the standard 7b travel head but a full Pro 7 Head) 
(1) Pro Grid Zoom Reflector 
(1) Profoto Head Extension Cable - 16' (this are included in the total price - retail $375) 
(1) Battery Charger (Multi-voltage: 90-250VAC) 
 
The Pro 7b generator gives you all the advantages of a heavy duty Profoto studio generator in a portable powerhouse. The 12V battery has a capacity of 250 full power flashes, and can be instantly replenished with spare battery in a special interchangeable cassette, or fully charged in 5 1/2 hours with the supplied AC charger or via a car cigarette lighter in 2.5 hours. Partial charging is also possible as batteries do not have a memory. 
 
The kit has been actively used and shows signs of it but Profoto is legendary for building solid, reliable gear and everything is in good working condition. The kit sold for over $3500 new plus the extra battery and head extension would cost $4000 new. 
 
Selling the kit for $1550 cash. 
 
Serious buyer only - no trades or money order scams etc. 
If it is still listed online it is available. 
If you are interested email. 
 
We are also selling other Profoto Lighting Accessories including the coveted Profoto 7b Universal Power Adaptor that allows you to plug the Pro-7b pack into the wall so you can shoot with it like a regular AC pack. This makes the pack both a location and studio kit. Take a look at our other items for sale for a bulk discount.

title: 2013 Felt Edict Pro Carbon $5499 retail Mountain trail bike
description:
Selling my gorgeous top of the line carbon Felt Edict Pro cross country mountain bike. 
Features full Shimano Deore XT components. 
 
Carbon fiber is lighter, and several times stronger than aluminum, steel, and even titanium. About 23lbs weight! 
 
Heres an assignment, go to any bike shop and see any full carbon mountain bike with XT parts (which are only second to the best Shimano XTR). Now look at the price tag. Is it six, seven, eight grand? Maybe even a wopping ten grand?! But its basically the same bike as you're getting here for over double - triple the price! 
 
Felt bikes aren't as well known as say Cannondale or Niner, but their bikes are just as well made, if not better. Where Felt really shines is in their unified designs. Every part is hand picked for performance, and the designers spend extra time creating the color palette to make a truly gorgeous works of art. The Edict it the perfect representation, whether the beautiful carbon color weave visible throughout the frame, down to all the contrasting orange bling that really sets the bike off. 
 
This is 2013 model year bike that retailed for $5500. I picked it in 2014 for bit less. 
I rode the bike a bunch the last two years, but the bike's still in good shape, with a ton of life left in her! 
 
Also spent an additional grand last year on upgrading the wheels to Mavics top of the line Crossmax SSC SLR 's! 
 
Full specs can be seen here..... 
http://2013.feltracing.com/USA/2013/Mountain/Edict-Six-Series/Edict-Pro.aspx 
 
Here's a nice video of how the bike is made, and in action..... 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gTm_TQoinn0 
 
There's still plenty of good weather around! Do some mountain biking while its still here.  
 
Asking $2950 
 
Will consider considerate offers.
